                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14693031" author="catholicon" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2015 06:55:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think while falling back, we should also log a message (warn???) so that app developer at least knows what to look for when authorizable node doesn&apos;t get created where she intended to.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14693040" author="anchela" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2015 07:05:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;alternatively we can also throw a &lt;tt&gt;ConstraintViolationException&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;IllegalArgumentException&lt;/tt&gt;; i just felt that it would be nicer to not throw. but i don&apos;t have a strong preference here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14693041" author="catholicon" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2015 07:09:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I too don&apos;t have a strong preference one way or the other... but, I&apos;d tend slightly towards &lt;tt&gt;IllegalArgumentException&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14693179" author="anchela" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2015 09:07:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed at r1695450.&lt;br/&gt;
an intermediate path resolving to the configured user/group root (either by passing in empty string or the corresponding absolute is path) is treated like &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
note, that while writing some tests i additionally found a bug in &lt;tt&gt;NodeUtil.addOrCreateTree&lt;/tt&gt; that would result in a path containing a parent or current path element; fixed as well and added a dedicated &lt;tt&gt;NodeUtil&lt;/tt&gt; test class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14706615" author="edivad" created="Fri, 21 Aug 2015 12:12:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for 1.3.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
